translated: Limhamn, Malmö. Born in 1901. Married Aina Ullenius in 1933. Children: Jan-Yngve born in 1934, Ann-Carin in 1935, Els-Marie in 1938, Eva-Brita in 1944. Studied at Lund University, graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in 1925, completed theology studies, practical theology exam, and was ordained as a priest in Linköping Diocese in 1930. Served as a pastor in Virserum, church assistant in Bredestad in 1931, diocesan assistant in 1937, temporary vicar in Askeryd in 1939, and vicar in Bredestad, Askeryd, and Marbäck from 1941. Served as chairman of the church meetings in Bredestad and Marbäck. Also, served as chairman of the school boards in Bredestad, Marbäck, and Askeryd. Vice-chairman of Aneby Municipal Council, county representative for the information board.
